Ask HN: How long does it take you to prototype a new tool?
text:
I think I am similar to many engineers in that I have a long list of side projects that I have built and would like to build. I recently noticed that it can take me a while to get going because of my expectation for the length of time to get a new project off the ground -- even if I choose a fairly standard/modern stack.

I'm curious how much time/effort people put into a fun "side project" before it gets to an alpha stage. A night? A weekend? A week?

If your answer is "it depends", imagine an app that does the following:

- Standard sign-up/sign in - CRUD on creating a list of items - You receive a single item from each list at a given frequency

Or any other simple app you can name

title: Ask HN: Do you think co's should be req'd to have a plastic/e-waste rtrn policy?
text:
Meaning ; a policy which requires items bought from a company should be able to be returned to a company for their e-waste cycles?

I have a ten-pound bag of shitty iPhone cables that are all defunct from the first day the iPhone was released...

I think its time to require ALL tech companies to have an e-waste bucket in any store that sells you a thing to take them back.

Thoughts?
